
############GIT BRANCH MERGE
Git branch merge #which means putting the branches of git together!
ğŸ’–merge branches:
âœ¨we have the emergency fix ready#we are ready for the emergency fix,and so merge the master#main branch and emergency-fix(ç´§æ€¥ä¿®å¤) branches

ğŸ’•change to the master branch:
  [user@localhost]$
git checkout master
Swiched to branch 'master'
  
ğŸ’•merge the current branch(master) with emergency-fix branch:
  [user@localhost]$
   git merge emergency-fix
   Updating 09f4acd..dfa79db
   Fast-forward
    index.html| 2+-
    1 file changed,1 insertion(+),1 deletion(-)
  
ğŸ˜‚Since the emergency-fix branch came directly from master,and no other changes had been made to master while we were working,Git sees this as a continuation of master.So it can
"Fast-forward",just pointing both master and emergency-fix to the same commit.

ğŸ˜As master and emergency-fix are essentially the same now,we can delete emergency-fix,as it is no longer needed:
[user@localhost]$ 
git branch -d emergency-fix
Deleted branch emergency-fix (was dfa79db)  

Merge Conflict
move over to hello-world-images and keep working.#è½¬åˆ°hello-world-imageså¹¶ç»§ç»­å·¥ä½œ
Add another image file(img_hello_git.jpg)
change index.html
[user@localhost]$
git checkout hello-world-images
Swiched to branch'hello-world-images'

ğŸ˜Šexample:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Hello World!"</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="bluestyle.css">
</head>
</body>
<h1>Hello world!</h1>
<div><img src ="img_hello_world.jpg" alt="Hello world from space" stype="width:100%;max-width:960px"></div>
<p>This is the first file in my new Git Repo.</p>
<p>Aa new line in out file!</p>
<div><img src="img_hello_git.jpg" alt="Hello Git"  style="width:100%;max-width:960px"></div>
</body>
</html>

Now we are done with our work here and can stage and commit for this branch:(ä¸ºè¿™ä¸ªåˆ†æ”¯æš‚å­˜å’Œæäº¤)
ğŸ’–git add --all
  git commit -m "added new image"
[hello-world-images 1f1584e] added new image
2 files changed, 1 insertion(+)
creat mode 100644 img_hello_git.jpg

we see that index.html has been changed in both branches.
Now we are ready to merge hello-world-images into master.
what will happen to the changes we recently made in master?
